&lt;br&gt;<br>
How we came to be!&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
Druid Airlines flight 666 was en route to Hong Kong (old airport).&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt; <br>
Captain Bruce Ganglion turns to Co-pilot Karl Grossemane and says, &quot;Okay we know this is going to be a tough one, its our first time into this airport. Its a difficult approach and a very short runway. We will come in really slow using full flaps and as soon as we touch down I will apply full brakes. You will apply full reverse thrust. If we do this successfully I'll be really pleased and everyone will think I am a hero so make sure you donÅft make a mistake.&quot;[large sound of inhalation]&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
<br>
Co-pilot Karl Grossemane notices the captain had turned a mild shade of blue towards the end of that speech but says nothing, he is used to the ramblings of his captain. &quot;Captain&quot;, asks Co-pilot Karl Grossemane , &quot;I fully recommend deploying a thermo-nuclear device just in front of our plane after touchdown. Don't you agree that this will provide the ultimate braking system? I could open the window, lob out a small one, then use an old garbage can lid to absorb the blast.&quot;&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
&quot;Don't you freaking well disagree with me you moron!! NO NUKES&quot;, yells the captain.&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
&quot;NOT FOR SPACE! JUST TO SLOW DOWN THE AIRCRAFT IDIOT!!&quot;, shouts Karl Grossemane.&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
So, while continuing to shout insults at each other, they begin their descent into the airport. They look out of the window and see the shortest runway they have ever seen. Co-pilot Karl Grossemane once again asserts, &quot;We have got to use a nuke, captain moron, Sir, there is no other freaking alternative, its the only reasonable way for us to be successful.&quot;&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
&quot;Listen you total imbecile if you disagree with me just one more time I will personally abuse you on the internet for the next one million years. I am the supreme intelligence here and if you dont like it you can take a freaking jump without a freaking parachute.&quot; Yells Captain Bruce Ganglion.&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
&quot;Hah, I don't care 'cos I have this handy pocket-sized nuclear weapon with which to cushion my fall.&quot; replies Co-pilot Karl Grossemane.&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
Despite the arguments, they get lined up on final approach with only 50 feet left to go. Things are getting tense as the captain gets the wheels to touch down just inches after the start of the runway.&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
Immediately, Captain Bruce Ganglion stamps on the brakes, Co-pilot Karl Grossemane slams the engines into full reverse thrust and the plane shudders and howls as the speed comes down. The end of the runway gets closer, beads of sweat on the brows of both our heroes combine into streams that run down and soak their collars. The passengers are screaming as luggage breaks free of the overhead lockers. People are saying their final prayers as they expect to die. Oh, the humanity!!&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
But, just as disaster seems inevitable, the plane grinds to a halt with millimeters to spare.&lt;br&gt; <br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
The noise subsides, the dust settles, and with a quivering voice, Captain Bruce Ganglion looks over to the Co-pilot and says, &quot;Freaking @#%$!! that has got to be the shortest runway in the world.&quot;&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
And, glancing from left to right, Co-pilot Karl Grossemane replies, &lt;br&gt;&quot;Yeah!!, but look how freaking wide it is!!&quot; &lt;br&gt;<br>
<br>
&lt;br&gt;Having shared this near death experience our two heroes become the best of friends and decide to work together in the fight against nuclear power in the skies. The source of the argument which nearly resulted in their untimely demise.&lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;br&gt;<br>
Stay tuned for more adventures from Bruce Ganglion and his sidekick Karl Grossemane. Defenders of the Earth and all round good eggs.<br>
